      <h4>The <i>Anti-Consultancy</i> Model</h4>

      <p>Fair warning, we take a practical, rational, and value-centric approach to our work. We look out for what's actually in your best interests. This means expressing our opinions regarding features we believe are unnecessary or should be deferred.</p>

      <blockquote><b><i>In fact, we'll often tell you to cut​ features instead of add them.</i></b></blockquote>

      <p>It’s an “anti-consultancy model”; developers typically push clients to add more features which translates to higher revenues for themselves. That's not what we do, we question whether a feature will bring you value. And you can use us as little or as much as you want.

      <p>Our clients seem to appreciate this - take a look at our <a href="/#testimonials">testimonials</a>. Because of this approach, we are selective about who we work with.</p>

